 To create a C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word, follow these steps:

### 1. Include necessary libraries

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>
#include <map>
#include <regex>
```

### 2. Define the main function

```cpp
int main() {
    // Define the target word
    std::string target_word = "example";

    // Open the input file
    std::ifstream file("input.txt");

    // Check if the file is open
    if (!file.is_open()) {
        std::cerr << "Error: Unable to open the input file." << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }

    // Create a regex object for the target word
    std::regex word_regex(target_word);

    // Initialize a counter for the number of occurrences
    size_t count = 0;

    // Read the file line by line
    std::string line;
    while (std::getline(file, line)) {
        // Find all occurrences of the target word in the current line
        std::sregex_iterator search_begin(line.begin(), line.end(), word_regex);
        std::sregex_iterator search_end;

        // Increment the counter for each occurrence
        count += std::distance(search_begin, search_end);
    }

    // Close the input file
    file.close();

    // Print the number of occurrences
    std::cout << "The word '" << target_word << "' occurs " << count << " times in the file." << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

### 3. Save the code to a file named `word_counter.cpp`

### 4. Compile and run the program

```sh
g++ -o word_counter word_counter.cpp
./word_counter
```

### 5. Create an input file named `input.txt` with the following content:

```
This is an example text file.
It contains multiple examples of the target word.
```

